üå± Stage 1 ‚Äî Foundations (1‚Äì2 months)

Goal: Build strong fundamentals in math, programming, and data handling.

1. Math Essentials

Statistics: distributions, probability, hypothesis testing

Linear algebra: vectors, matrices

Calculus basics: derivatives, gradients

2. Python Fundamentals

Python basics: variables, loops, functions

Libraries: NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib

Writing clean code

Git & GitHub for version control

3. Starter Projects

Exploratory data analysis on simple Kaggle datasets

Create visualizations (histograms, scatterplots, boxplots)

Basic data cleaning (missing values, outliers)

Checkpoint:

‚úî Comfortable with Python and data manipulation
‚úî Can analyze and visualize real datasets

üöÄ Stage 2 ‚Äî Core Machine Learning (2‚Äì3 months)

Goal: Learn classic ML algorithms and build strong foundations.

4. Supervised Learning

Linear regression, logistic regression

Decision Trees, Random Forests

Gradient boosting: XGBoost, LightGBM

5. Model Evaluation

Train/validation/test split

Cross-validation

Accuracy, precision/recall, F1-score

ROC/AUC, confusion matrix

6. Unsupervised Learning

Clustering: KMeans, DBSCAN

Dimensionality reduction: PCA

Anomaly detection basics

Projects

Predict house prices

Classify customer churn

Cluster customers into segments

Forecast sales or demand

Checkpoint:

‚úî Can build and evaluate ML models
‚úî Can explain results and model performance

ü§ñ Stage 3 ‚Äî Deep Learning & NLP (2‚Äì3 months)

Goal: Learn modern AI tools and neural networks.

7. Deep Learning Basics

Frameworks: PyTorch or TensorFlow

Neural network fundamentals

CNNs for images

RNN/LSTM/GRU for sequences

8. Natural Language Processing (NLP)

Tokenization, embeddings

Word2Vec, TF-IDF

Transformer models (BERT, DistilBERT)

Text classification, sentiment analysis

Projects

Text sentiment classifier

Image classifier (cats vs dogs)

Product review analyzer

Simple chatbot or FAQ assistant

Checkpoint:

‚úî Can train deep learning models
‚úî Understand basic transformer fine-tuning

üß† Stage 4 ‚Äî Data Engineering & MLOps (2‚Äì4 months)

Goal: Learn to deploy, automate, and scale data projects.

9. Data Engineering

SQL (MySQL, Postgres)

Data pipelines (Airflow/Prefect)

Cloud platforms (AWS/GCP/Azure)

Building APIs with FastAPI or Flask

10. MLOps

Model deployment

Docker

MLflow for experiment tracking

Monitoring & data drift detection

Continuous integration (GitHub Actions)

Projects

Build an ETL pipeline

Deploy a model as an API

Create a live dashboard

Automate a daily data workflow

Checkpoint:

‚úî Can deploy ML models
‚úî Understand how real-world systems run

üèÜ Stage 5 ‚Äî Specialization (choose 1‚Äì2)

Once the foundations are strong, choose a specialization:

A. NLP Specialist

RAG systems

Vector search (FAISS, Pinecone)

Fine-tuning LLMs

Chatbot systems

B. Machine Learning Engineer

Distributed training

Model optimization

Large-scale API deployment

C. Data Scientist (Business Focus)

Experiment design (A/B testing)

Causal inference

Forecasting and time series

Business storytelling

D. Analytics & BI

Tableau / Power BI

KPI dashboards

Story-driven analysis

